User Request: A user sends a request to the Flask API.Flask Processing: Flask processes the request and determines if a dbt run is needed.Trigger dbt: Flask can trigger a Kubernetes Job to run dbt commands.This can be done by creating a new Job resource in Kubernetes via the Kubernetes API from Flask.dbt Execution: The dbt Job runs the specified dbt commands (e.g., dbt run, dbt test).Results Handling: dbt processes the data, and the results are stored in the configured data warehouse.Response: Flask can query the data warehouse for results (if needed) and send the response back to the user.